File: Eskom has implemented power cuts. Unsplash/Johannes Plenio JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has implemented stage two power cuts from 4pm Sunday afternoon. The power utility says the blackouts will continue until 5 am on Wednesday. This is after rolling blackouts were suspended on Friday. READ: Eskom to implement Stage 2 power cuts from 5pm Eskom says the loss of four additional power generation units over the past 24 hours, And the delay in some units returning to service has resulted in the implementation of power cuts. It's warning that any further deterioration in generation capacity could lead to higher stages of blackouts Eskom implements Stage 2 power cuts from 4PM this afternoon until 5AM on Wednesday. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/E37dE241qh